              <span id="reviewTextContainer1470082501" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9666833055180531889">This medieval story has a modern feel to it so that its message becomes timeless. This most dysfunctional family celebrates Christmas with betrayal and love, if not in equal parts, then with equal fervor. <br/><br/>The best review of the play I read included the line, &quot;King Lear&quot; meets &quot;Who&apos;s Afraid of Virginia Woolf?&quot;<br/><br/>Recommended, especially because the Hepburn/O&apos;Toole film does not have English subtitles and the word play is too precious to guess at.</span>
  <span id="freeText9666833055180531889" style="display:none">This medieval story has a modern feel to it so that its message becomes timeless. This most dysfunctional family celebrates Christmas with betrayal and love, if not in equal parts, then with equal fervor. <br /><br />The best review of the play I read included the line, "King Lear" meets "Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?"<br /><br />Recommended, especially because the Hepburn/O'Toole film does not have English subtitles and the word play is too precious to guess at.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9666833055180531889" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


